<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a49c4e1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s4912"><num value="4912">§ 4912.</num><heading> Fees and access</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall provide reasonable public services and access (including electronic access) to any information maintained as part of the Data Bank and may charge reasonable fees consistent with <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s552">section 552 of title 5</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a49c4e2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/418/tV/s5412">Pub. L. 100–418, title V, § 5412</ref>, <date date="1988-08-23">Aug. 23, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/1467">102 Stat. 1467</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
